                    <ab>
                        <title>Exodus 1</title>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="87r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l>Book of Exodus</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="1">And these are the names
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            of the sons of Israel, who came to Egypt.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            With Jacob, each came with the people of his house: </l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah, </l>
                        <l n="3">Issachar, Zebulun, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            Benjamin, </l>
                        <l n="4">Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.</l>
                        <l n="5">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            all souls who came out from Jacob’s thigh were seventy souls, with
                            Joseph
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            who was in Egypt. </l>
                        <l n="6">And Joseph died, and all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            his brothers, and all that generation. </l>
                        <l n="7">And the sons of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            spread, and multiplied, and increased, and grew very, very strong,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            and the land was filled with them. </l>
                        <l n="8">And a new king rose
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            over Egypt, who knew not Joseph. </l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            And he said to his people, ‘Lo, the people of the sons of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            are more and stronger than we. </l>
                        <l n="10">Come,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            let us deal wisely with them, maybe it will increase, and it shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            if war befall us, and it, too, will be added to our enemies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            and the will fight against us and will go out from the land.’ </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="11">And they set over them tax collector, rulers
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            to oppress them with their burdens. And they built
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            for Pharaoh treasure cities, Pithom and Raamses.
                            <milestone unit="page" n="87v" />
                        </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="12">But the more they oppressed them, the more they multiplied
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and the more spread. And they weakened before the sons of Israel. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="13">And the Egyptians made the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            sons of Israel to serve oppressively. </l>
                        <l n="14">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            they made their lives bitter with hard service, in clay,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            and in brick, and in all manner of hard service in the field:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            all their service, in which they made them serve, was oppressive. </l>
                        <l n="15">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            And the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            midwives, of whom the name of one was Shiphrah, and the name of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            second was Puah, </l>
                        <l n="16">And Pharaoh said, ‘When you make Hebrew women give birth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            and see them in the place for giving birth:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            if it is a son, then you shall kill him, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            if it is a daughter, then she shall live.’ </l>
                        <l n="17">But
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            the midwives feared God, and did not as
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            the king of Egypt spoke to them, and they kept alive
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            also the male children. </l>
                        <l n="18">And the king of Egypt called for the midwives,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            and he said to them, ‘Why have you done this thing,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and have let the male children alive?’ </l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            And the midwives said to Pharaoh, ‘Because the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women, because they are healthy,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            they give birth before the midwife comes to them.’ </l>
                        <l n="20">And
                            <milestone unit="page" n="88r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            God dealt well with the midwives. And the people multiplied, and grew
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            very strong, </l>
                        <l n="21">And it was because the midwives feared
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            God, and he gave them rest. </l>
                        <l n="22">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, ‘Every son who
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            is born: you shall cast into the Nile. And every daughter you shall keep
                            alive.’ </l>
                    </ab>
